  <p>My non-negotiable pre-roll ritual, run before every single take: headphones on, hear the recorder rolling, glance at the levels, check the mic's close and there's no boom shadow, listen for any noise in the room right now. Four seconds. On a frantic day it's the first thing that gets skipped and the exact thing that saves you — because the take you didn't check is the one where the recorder wasn't armed, or the battery died, or the AC clicked on. Make the ritual automatic and you'll never drive home from a shoot with a card full of silence or a scene full of hiss.</p>
